Oarm. X. — Ad Mercurium.

Aeonum—Mercury, thou who in their infancy didst tame the human race by the gifts of speech and gymnastic exercises, of thee will I sing, thou messen- ger of the gods, thou master of the lyre and prince of thieves. Why, while Apollo was threatening thee for stealing his cows, he turned and laughed to find his quiver gone. By thee Priam passed through the Grecian camp.
